        hey merry xmas mates!  too bad we can't check any replies on disqus esp. for those of us that can't be here each wk...

        & that's awesome about mariah!!  back in the 90s on the billboard hot 100 chart, you all should've seen how often she would be in the top 10!  she had hit after hit after hit!  & back in the day, when you had a big hit, it'd be forever 'til it fell out of the top 10.  i have lots of fond memories of mariah dominating the hot 100 top 10 week after week after week.  

        & same with george michael...back during this time back in 1987, his 'faith' album was fast becoming a huge success!  & all thoughout 1988 he was hands down 1 of the biggest recording acts here in the states.  he was up there with prince, michael jackson, madonna, whitney, janet, bon jovi, def leppard and the list goes on.  my fave musical year of the 80s!!  everyone had a hit that year over here ;)
